usführungen zu indigenen Völkern und Sprachen, die Hispanisierung Amerikas, Thesen der sprachlichen Differenzierung, die Ausbildung hispanoamerikanischer Merkmale, das Spanische in den USA. Neben einem aktualisierten Literaturverzeichnis enthält der Band auch einen praktischen Übungsteil.  aInterest in the Spanish language and its regional varieties is increasing constantly. This book, aimed at students of Romance and Spanish Studies, gives a detailed description of American Spanish both regionally and historically, contrasting it with the European norm. It contains an updated bibliography and a number of useful exercises.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aLanguages in contactzAmerica. 0aSpanish languagexDialectszAmerica. 4aAmerika. 4aSpanisch. 4aVarietätenlinguistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aLanguage Variation.  aSpanish.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074296108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2014z9783110370270oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103740940 cprintz978311034038940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311034039640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110340396423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110340396/original  a978-3-11-074296-1  De Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014  aZDB-23-DSPb2